commitResults.messageBody:
The code lacks java assertions, making it challenging to document
assumptions which are critical at various points in the code.

Adding java assertions is crucial for documenting assumptions. It
helps identify and also prevent unexpected issues during
development and runtime.

This commit introduces java assertions at key points in the codebase.

This enhances code clarity and maintainability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to enhance code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
Code has some inaccurate naming which could be misleading.
Changed existing variable names to make it more accurate.

Changes made:
* Renamed the variable "lst" to "taskList" to provide a more descriptive and intuitive name for the task list
* Renamed the variable "idx" to "taskIdx" to make it clearer that it represents the index of a task
* Renamed the variable "by" to "endTime" to better convey its purpose as the end time of an event task

This enhances code maintainability and readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add contact management feature to support add, remove and view contacts
commitResults.messageBody:
GeraldBot did not support contact management previously.

Changes made:
* Enable adding new contacts into contact list.
* Enable removing existing contacts from contact list.
* Enable displaying existing contact list.

This feature enables contact management for GeraldBot.
